WEBVTT

00:11.804 --> 00:14.261
MOHINDER: (NARRA TING)
The sun rises on a new dawn,

00:16.893 --> 00:21.557
yet few us realize the debt
we owe to those responsible
for this,

00:21.647 --> 00:28.268
to those who dwell among us,
anonymous, seeming/y ordinary,

00:28.529 --> 00:32.442
whom destiny brought together
to repair, to heal,

00:32.533 --> 00:35.366
to save us from ourselves.

00:36.787 --> 00:39.449
MOHINDER: If evolution can
do this for even
the smallest of creatures,

00:39.540 --> 00:41.701
then why not
these human beings?

00:41.792 --> 00:45.785
If someone here
found out about me,
what would happen?

00:45.880 --> 00:47.245
When will they stop?

00:47.340 --> 00:48.420
I don't know.

00:48.841 --> 00:52.459
She's a shiny new toy,
and she's all mine.

00:54.013 --> 00:56.971
MOHINDER: (NARRA TING) And
they’re still out there
among us

00:57.058 --> 00:59.219
in the shadows, in the light.

00:59.310 --> 01:01.972
We pass them on the street
without a glance,

01:02.063 --> 01:04.600
never suspecting,
never knowing.

01:05.316 --> 01:07.523
Do they even know yet

01:09.070 --> 01:12.233
that they are bound together
by a common purpose,

01:12.323 --> 01:16.987
a glaring reality,
to be extraordinary?

01:17.161 --> 01:21.154
MOHINDER: Teleportation,
tissue regeneration. These
are no longer simply theories.

01:21.249 --> 01:23.581
l have seen them
with my own eyes.

01:23.876 --> 01:25.741
MOHINDER: (NARRA TING)
And when destiny
does anoint them...

01:25.836 --> 01:28.828
My name is Hiro Nakamura.
I'm from the future.

01:29.257 --> 01:30.918
...how do they
hide from it?

01:31.008 --> 01:32.168
You may feel confined here,

01:32.260 --> 01:35.673
but this is far freer
a cage than the one
they'd put you in.

01:35.846 --> 01:39.464
MOHINDER: (NARRA TING) How long
can they dwell in the shadows
before either fate

01:39.558 --> 01:44.643
or their own flawed
humanity draws them out
into the light again?

01:45.314 --> 01:48.932
And how will they know
what awaits them
when it finally does?

01:52.154 --> 01:55.772
And not only
are these special
individuals among us,

01:55.866 --> 01:57.447
they bear a curse,

01:57.535 --> 02:00.447
a virus which
strips them
of their powers

02:01.706 --> 02:03.287
andleadsto
their eventual death.

02:03.374 --> 02:06.832
In the last few months,
I have discovered what
I believe to be a plague.

02:06.919 --> 02:10.161
A plague which targets
only these unique individuals.

02:10.256 --> 02:12.838
It's a disease which threatens
to eradicate them all,

02:12.925 --> 02:17.510
and in doing so, deprives
our species of its
evolutionary advancement.

02:17.596 --> 02:20.963
Without this advancement,
the challenges
of the modern world,

02:21.058 --> 02:24.391
global warming, terrorism,
diminishing resources,

02:24.478 --> 02:28.221
seem almost insurmountable
on our thin shoulders.

02:28.774 --> 02:32.062
The fate of humanity itself
hangs in the balance.

02:32.153 --> 02:34.485
But with proper funding
and research,

02:34.572 --> 02:36.654
we can stop
the advancement
of this disease.

02:36.741 --> 02:39.528
I urge each and every one
of you to take up this cause,

02:39.618 --> 02:44.032
spread the word
and fight those who would
keep the world from the truth.

02:44.582 --> 02:46.573
Thank you all for coming.

02:52.923 --> 02:55.050
Inspirational lecture,
Dr. Suresh.

02:55.134 --> 02:57.967
l was wondering
if I could trouble you
for an autograph.

02:58.054 --> 03:00.636
Your father would have
been so proud.

03:01.098 --> 03:02.929
So would your sister.

03:04.769 --> 03:06.475
Who the hell are you
and why are you following me?

03:06.562 --> 03:08.063
This isn't necessary.
I'm nobody.

03:08.147 --> 03:09.227
What, you think
I didn't recognize you?

03:09.273 --> 03:11.013
You've been at three
of my lectures.
Yeah.

03:11.108 --> 03:13.520
The Company send you
to bag and tag me?
Is that it?

03:13.611 --> 03:15.192
A year ago
I would've run.
But not anymore.

03:15.279 --> 03:19.613
That's good. Because if you
had, I wouldn't be able
to offer you a job.

03:22.620 --> 03:26.112
I've been down
that road before.
It doesn't end well.

03:26.707 --> 03:28.868
Where will you go,
Dr. Suresh?

03:28.959 --> 03:31.371
No one even believes
they exist.

03:32.129 --> 03:35.667
I found your father's book
in the parapsychology section,

03:35.758 --> 03:38.966
in between hypnosis
and alien abductions.

03:39.053 --> 03:42.796
They don't take you seriously.
They all think you're nuts.

03:44.308 --> 03:45.639
But not me.

03:46.602 --> 03:49.844
So if you're really
interested in saving
the world,

03:50.481 --> 03:53.644
the least you could do
is let me buy you a drink.

