a moral imperative
to protect your species.

24:22.712 --> 24:24.794
It doesn't matter
one way or the other
about Sylar.

24:24.881 --> 24:27.042
He's no longer a threat.
He's dead.

24:27.133 --> 24:29.294
And now you have Molly.

24:30.887 --> 24:34.880
You and Matt Parkman
are protecting her.

24:35.516 --> 24:39.008
Now, we're not interfering
with that arrangement.
Far from it.

24:39.270 --> 24:41.306
We're offering to help you.

24:41.397 --> 24:45.060
We have resources
to offer you, Dr. Suresh.

24:45.735 --> 24:49.569
The plague you talked about,
the disease which killed
your sister, Shanti.

24:49.656 --> 24:51.396
The virus.
Yes.

24:52.158 --> 24:55.867
We have the funds
you need for your research.

24:56.871 --> 24:57.951
Now,

24:58.414 --> 25:00.826
can you imagine
what would happen

25:01.959 --> 25:07.295
if that virus mutated
and crossed over
into the general population?

25:08.800 --> 25:12.509
Look, the type of research
you're talking about
is extremely expensive.

25:12.595 --> 25:15.428
Trust me, that won't
be a problem.

25:21.270 --> 25:25.058
Let's just say
we have our own
private Fort Knox.

25:28.653 --> 25:31.770
So, can we count you in?

25:37.120 --> 25:38.485
Thank you.
DELIVERY BOY: You're welcome.

25:39.539 --> 25:40.654
Dinner!

25:42.667 --> 25:45.625
Shouldn't I be eating
some vegetables
every once in a while?

25:45.712 --> 25:49.204
(LAUGHS) Well, that is why
I got you a vegetable pizza,
smarty pants.

25:49.298 --> 25:51.334
Plus, I got your favorite,
Rocky Road, for dessert.

25:51.426 --> 25:54.259
You're just trying
to bribe me because
you never cook.

25:54.345 --> 25:56.586
I miss Mohinder.
He cooks.

25:56.681 --> 25:58.046
Hey. I can cook.

25:58.141 --> 26:01.759
