to the branch of a tree

36:47.915 --> 36:49.746
and start to pick off
the blackguards,
one by one.

36:49.833 --> 36:51.334
That's fighting dirty.

36:51.418 --> 36:53.500
That's fighting smart, sir.

36:54.088 --> 36:55.999
I give him a fair wage.

36:56.673 --> 36:58.129
If he lives.

37:01.470 --> 37:03.586
No. This can't be.

37:05.140 --> 37:07.301
No. I come from the future.

37:07.810 --> 37:09.471
Many years from now.

37:09.561 --> 37:11.813
Your noble deeds
become part of our history.

37:11.897 --> 37:13.353
(LAUGHS) The future?
Yes.

37:13.440 --> 37:14.429
That's a good one.

37:14.525 --> 37:17.437
No, it is true.
I know what
happens to you.

37:17.820 --> 37:22.063
As a boy I read the book,
The Trials of Takezo Kensei.

37:22.157 --> 37:25.399
How you killed
the Black Bear
of Sakashita,

37:25.494 --> 37:28.031
your love of
the swordsmith's
daughter,

37:28.122 --> 37:31.580
and you defeat the terrible
white-bearded warlord

37:31.667 --> 37:33.908
and saved
the village of Otsu.

37:34.503 --> 37:35.492
Otsu?

37:35.587 --> 37:36.622
Do you smell smoke?

37:46.682 --> 37:48.047
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

37:56.733 --> 37:58.894
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

38:00.070 --> 38:02.061
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

39:14.686 --> 39:16.267
Let me see it.

39:21.276 --> 39:23.858
KAITO: I do not take
death threats idly.

39:23.946 --> 39:25.186
Someone is
playing a trick.

39:26.031 --> 39:27.487
Are they?

39:27.574 --> 39:32.034
Charles Deveaux,
Linderman, your husband,

39:32.663 --> 39:35.154
all of them dead.

39:37.125 --> 39:40.743
Now there are nine.

39:41.797 --> 39:44.539
